\u4e2a\u4e61\u30012\u4e2a\u9547\u30014\u4e2a\u573a\uff0c133\u4e2a\u884c\u653f\u6751\u300114\u4e2a\u793e\u533a\u3002{...}2016\u5e74\u672b\uff0c\u5168\u53bf\u603b\u6237\u6570\uff08\u542b\u5854\u897f\u5357\u52d8\u63a2\u5f00\u53d1\u516c\u53f8\uff0965684\u6237\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d\u53bf\u5c5e\u6237\u657059804\u6237\uff1b\u603b\u4eba\u53e3208950\u4eba\uff08\u542b\u5854\u897f\u5357\u52d8\u63a2\u5f00\u53d1\u516c\u53f8\uff09\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d\uff0c\u7ef4\u543e\u5c14\u65cf175686\u4eba\uff0c\u536084.1\uff05\uff0c\u6c49\u65cf27131\u4eba\uff0c\u536013\uff05\uff0c\u5854\u5409\u514b\u65cf4463\u4eba\uff0c\u53602.1\uff05\uff0c\u5176\u4ed6\u6c11\u65cf1670\u4eba\uff0c\u53600.8\uff05\u3002\u7537104471\u4eba\uff0c\u5973104479\u4eba\uff0c\u7537\u5973\u6027\u522b\u6bd4\u4e3a49.9:50.1\u3002\u4eba\u53e3\u51fa\u751f\u738716.97\u2030\uff0c\u81ea\u7136\u589e\u957f\u738711.55\u2030\u3002}}}}</ref><ref name=\"statsposkam\">{{cite web |url=http://www.stats.gov.cn/tjsj/tjbz/tjyqhdmhcxhfdm/2018/65/31/653124.html |script-title=zh:2018\u5e74\u7edf\u8ba1\u7528\u533a\u5212\u4ee3\u7801\u548c\u57ce\u4e61\u5212\u5206\u4ee3\u7801\uff1a\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf |language=zh-hans |publisher=[[National Bureau of Statistics of the People's Republic of China]] |date=2018 |accessdate=27 January 2020 |quote={{lang|zh-hans|\u7edf\u8ba1\u7528\u533a\u5212\u4ee3\u7801 \u540d\u79f0 653124100000 \u6cfd\u666e\u9547 653124101000 \u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u9547 653124200000 \u6ce2\u65af\u5580\u6728\u4e61 653124201000 \u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u4f9d\u739b\u4e61 653124202000 \u53e4\u52d2\u5df4\u683c\u4e61 653124203000 \u8d5b\u529b\u4e61 653124204000 \u4f9d\u80af\u82cf\u4e61 653124205000 \u56fe\u547c\u5176\u4e61 653124206000 \u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u4e61 653124207000 \u963f\u514b\u5854\u6728\u4e61 653124208000 \u963f\u4f9d\u5e93\u52d2\u4e61 653124209000 \u5e03\u4f9d\u9c81\u514b\u5854\u5409\u514b\u65cf\u4e61 653124210000 \u6850\u5b89\u4e61 653124400000 \u519c\u573a\u573a\u90e8 653124401000 \u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u826f\u79cd\u573a 653124402000 \u56ed\u827a\u573a 653124403000 \u56fd\u8425\u6797\u573a|}}}}</ref>\n\nTowns ({{lang|ug|\u0628\u0627\u0632\u0649\u0631\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u9547}})\n*[[Poskam Town]]<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/aroundafghanista00debouoft/page/n219|pages=105\u2013106|title=Around Afghanistan|author=\u00c9mile Antoine Henry de Bouillane de Lacoste|date=1909|via=[[Internet Archive]]|translator=J. G. Anderson|publisher=Sir Isaac Pitman & Sons, Ltd.|location=London}}</ref> (Zepu;<ref name=\"3rdedition\">{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/CompleteAtlasOfTheWorld3rdEdition2016/page/n239|title=Complete Atlas Of The World|edition=3|publisher=[[Penguin Random House]]|page=238|quote=Zepu|via=[[Internet Archive]]|date=2016|isbn=978-1-4654-4401-1}}</ref> {{lang|ug|\u067e\u0648\u0633\u0643\u0627\u0645 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0649\u0631\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u6cfd\u666e\u9547}}), K\u00fcybagh Town (Kuiyibage; {{lang|ug|\u0643\u06c8\u064a\u0628\u0627\u063a \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0649\u0631\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u9547}})\nTownships ({{lang|ug|\u064a\u06d0\u0632\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u4e61}})\n*[[Poskam Township]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fmprc.gov.cn/ce/cetur/eng/xwdt/t160708.htm|title=\"East Turkistan\" Terrorist Forces Cannot Get Away with Impunity|location=[[Beijing]]|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People's Republic of China]]|date=21 January 2002|accessdate=27 January 2020|quote=On December 30, 1999, the police discovered an underground hideout in Poskam Township, Zepu County. In this hideout, which was 3 meters from the ground and measured 3 meters long, 2 meters wide and 1.7 meters high, they found tools for making explosive devices, such as electric drills and electric welding machines, as well as blueprints and antitank grenades.}}</ref> (Bosikamu; {{lang|ug|\u067e\u0648\u0633\u0643\u0627\u0645 \u064a\u06d0\u0632\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u6ce2\u65af\u5580\u6728\u4e61}}), [[Zhima Township]] (Yima; {{lang|ug|\u0698\u0649\u0645\u0627 \u064a\u06d0\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u4f9d\u739b\u4e61}}), [[G\u00fclbagh Township]] (Gulebage; {{lang|ug|\u06af\u06c8\u0644\u0628\u0627\u063a \u064a\u0649\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u53e4\u52d2\u5df4\u683c\u4e61}}), [[Seyli Township]] (Saili; {{lang|ug|\u0633\u06d5\u064a\u0644\u0649 \u064a\u0649\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u8d5b\u529b\u4e61}}), [[Ikkisu Township]] (Yikesu; {{lang|ug|\u0626\u0649\u0643\u0643\u0649\u0633\u06c7 \u064a\u0649\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u4f9d\u514b\u82cf\u4e61}}), [[Tughchi Township]] (Tuhuqi; {{lang|ug|\u062a\u06c7\u063a\u0686\u0649 \u064a\u0649\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u56fe\u547c\u5176\u4e61}}), [[Aqtam Township]] (Aketamu; {{lang|ug|\u0626\u0627\u0642\u062a\u0627\u0645 \u064a\u0649\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u963f\u514b\u5854\u6728\u4e61}}), [[Aykol|Aykol Township]] (Ayikule, Ayk\u00f6l; {{lang|ug|\u0626\u0627\u064a\u0643\u06c6\u0644 \u064a\u0649\u0632\u0649\u0633\u0649\t}} / {{lang|zh-hans|{{linktext|\u963f\u4f9d\u5e93\u52d2|\u4e61}}}}), [[K\u00fcybagh Township]] (Kuiyibage; {{lang|ug|\u0643\u06c8\u064a\u0628\u0627\u063a \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0649\u0631\u0649}} / {{lang|zh-hans|\u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u4e61}})\nCounty-controlled district (\u53bf\u8f96\u533a)\n*[[Kuiyibage District]] (\u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u533a)\n\n==Economy==\nIrrigation is well-developed in the county, and the county is an important producer of wheat, rice, corn and cotton in southern Xinjiang. Grapes are a local speciality. Industries include mining, machinery, construction and cotton-spinning.<ref name=\"cihai\">{{cite book|editor1=\u590f\u5f81\u519c|editor2=\u9648\u81f3\u7acb|script-title=zh:\u8f9e\u6d77\uff1a\u7b2c\u516d\u7248\u5f69\u56fe\u672c |trans-title=[[Cihai]] (Sixth Edition in Color) |date=September 2009|location=\u4e0a\u6d77. [[Shanghai]]|publisher=\u4e0a\u6d77\u8f9e\u4e66\u51fa\u7248\u793e. [[Shanghai Lexicographical Publishing House]].|isbn=9787532628599| language=zh|pages=2857\u20132858| url=|quote={{lang|zh-hans|\u704c\u6e89\u53d1\u8fbe\uff0c\u4e3a\u5357\u7586\u91cd\u8981\u5c0f\u9ea6\u3001\u7a3b\u3001\u7389\u7c73\u548c\u68c9\u82b1\u4ea7\u533a\u3002\u7279\u4ea7\u8461\u8404\u3002\u5de5\u4e1a\u6709\u91c7\u77ff\u3001\u673a\u68b0\u3001\u5efa\u6750\u3001\u68c9\u7eba\u3002}}}}</ref> As of 2017, Poskam County had 42,405.25 hectares of [[arable land]].<ref name=\"poskamgaikuang\"/>\n\n===Tourism===\nA tourist attraction located in the county is Jinhuyang National Forest Park, rated as a [[AAAAA Tourist Attractions of China]] according to the official classification for tourist sights.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kashgar Jinhuyang Cultural and Tourism Festival kicks off|url=http://english.ts.cn/NationalUnity/2016-10/21/content_12388508_all.htm|work=[[Tianshannet]]|date=October 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of 2015, 181,256 of the 223,694 residents of the county were [[Uyghurs|Uyghur]], 35,950 were [[Han Chinese]] and 6,488 were from other ethnic groups.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.xjtj.gov.cn/sjcx/tjnj_3415/2016xjtjnj/rkjy/201707/t20170714_539450.html |script-title= zh:3-7 \u5404\u5730\u3001\u5dde\u3001\u5e02\u3001\u53bf(\u5e02)\u5206\u6c11\u65cf\u4eba\u53e3\u6570 |language=zh-hans||publisher={{lang|ug|\u0634\u0649\u0646\u062c\u0627\u06ad \u0626\u06c7\u064a\u063a\u06c7\u0631 \u0626\u0627\u067e\u062a\u0648\u0646\u0648\u0645 \u0631\u0627\u064a\u0648\u0646\u0649}} {{lang|zh-hans|\u65b0\u7586\u7ef4\u543e\u5c14\u81ea\u6cbb\u533a\u7edf\u8ba1\u5c40}} Statistic Bureau of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region |date=15 March 2017|access-date=3 September 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20171011101904/http://www.xjtj.gov.cn/sjcx/tjnj_3415/2016xjtjnj/rkjy/201707/t20170714_539450.html |archive-date= 11 October 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{{citation needed span|According to the 2002 census, it has a population of 180,000.|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Transportation==\nPoskam is served by [[China National Highway 315]] and the [[Kashgar-Hotan Railway]].\n\n\n==References==\n<references />\n{{commons category|Poskam County}}\n\n{{Xinjiang Administrative Divisions}}\n\n{{Coord|38|11|44|N|77|16|20|E|source:trwiki_region:CN-65_type:adm3rd|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:County-level divisions of Xinjiang]]\n[[Category:Kashgar Prefecture]]\n\n\n{{Xinjiang-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name = Poskam\n|native_name = {{lower|0.1em|{{nobold|{{lang|ug|\u067e\u0648\u0633\u0643\u0627\u0645 \u0646\u0627\u06be\u0649\u064a\u0649\u0633\u0649}}}}<br>{{lower|0.2em|{{lang|zh-hans|\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf}}}}}}\n|other_name = Zepu\n|settlement_type = [[County (People's Republic of China)|County]]\n|image_skyline = File:Poskam 8266390061 fae46a8f0a o.jpg\n|image_map = Location of Poskam within Xinjiang (China).png\n|map_caption = Location of Zepu/Poskam County (red) within Kashgar Prefecture (yellow) and Xinjiang\n|subdivision_type = Country\n|subdivision_name = [[China|People's Republic of China]]\n|subdivision_type1 = [[Autonomous regions of China|Autonomous region]]\n|subdivision_name1 = [[Xinjiang]]\n|subdivision_type2 = [[Prefectures of the People's Republic of China|Prefecture]]\n|subdivision_name2 = [[Kashgar Prefecture|Kashgar]] / Kashi\n| demographics_type2              = [[List of ethnic groups in China|Ethnic groups]]\n| demographics2_title1            = Major ethnic groups\n| demographics2_info1             = [[Uyghurs|Uyghur]], [[Han Chinese]]<ref name=\"govposkam\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xzqh.org/html/show/xj/21316.html|script-title=zh:1997\u5e74\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u884c\u653f\u533a\u5212|language=zh-hans|date=19 November 2010|accessdate=27 January 2020|website=XZQH.org|quote=\u7ef4\u543e\u5c14\u65cf\u536077.1\uff05\uff0c\u6c49\u65cf\u536020.4%\u3002}}</ref>\n|area_total_km2 = 987.97\n|area_footnotes =<ref name=\"poskamgaikuang\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xjzp.gov.cn/P/C/8348.htm|script-title=zh