ina.org.cn/travel/2014-01/09/content_31134388_12.htm|title=Rural tourism becomes popular in China|author=Wang Song|website=[[China Internet Information Center]]|quote=Performers of Uyghur ethnic group perform for tourists in Poskam County, northwest China's Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region, Oct. 19, 2011.|date=9 January 2014|accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2011-02/10/content_11973359.htm|title=Latest batch of officials head to Xinjiang|date=10 February 2011|accessdate=27 January 2020|website=[[China Daily]]|author=Shao Wei|quote=A worker lays bricks at a housing project for an assistance program in Poskam county of the Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region on Nov 13, 2010.}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Genetic diversity of Blastocystis in kindergarten children in southern Xinjiang, China|authors=Meng Qi, Zilin Wei, Ying Zhang, Qiyuan Zhang, Juanfeng Li, Longxian Zhang, Rongjun Wang|journal=[[Parasites & Vectors]]|date=11 January 2020|volume=13|issue=15|pages=15|doi=10.1186/s13071-020-3890-0|pmid=31924261|pmc=6954523|quote=Subtype ST3 was dominant in most of the counties surveyed, with ST1 appearing to be the predominant subtype in the Lop county and only ST1 being identified in the Poskam county (Table 1).}}</ref><ref name=\"GNISposkam\">{{GEOnet2|22C2872F69F442E3B94526182DA3C9A4|Poskam   (Approved - N)}}, [[National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency|United States National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency]]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/gov.gpo.fdsys.CHRG-110hhrg44748/page/n233|title=CONGRESSIONAL-EXECUTIVE COMMISSION ON CHINA ANNUAL REPORT 2008|author=Congressional-Executive Commission on China|date=31 October 2008|publisher=[[U.S. Government Printing Office]]|location=[[Washington, D.C.]]|via=[[Internet Archive]]|page=228|quote=Kashgar District Government (Online), \"Let Society Be Stable and Harmonious, For the People To Be Without Fear-Work Report on Poskam County Striving to Establish a Region-Level Quiet and Stable County\" [Rang shehui wending hexie wei baixing anjuleye-zepuxian zheng chuang zizhiquji ping'an xian gongzuo jishi], 3 December 07|author-link=Congressional-Executive Commission on China}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rfa.org/english/news/uyghur/petrol-06182013153821.html|title=Gas Stations in Xinjiang Bar Veil-Wearing Muslim Women|date=18 June 2013|accessdate=27 January 2020|authors=Yang Fan, Gulchehra Keyum, Luisetta Mudie|translator=Luisetta Mudie, Mamatjan Juma|publisher=[[Radio Free Asia]]|quote=A Uyghur woman in Kashgar's Poskam county said that dressing curbs for Muslim women were not new in her area, saying notices to the effect have been introduced even in hospitals and libraries.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=Us5wDwAAQBAJ|title=Identity, History and Trans-Nationality in Central Asia: The Mountain Communities of Pamir|editor=Dagikhudo Dagiev, Carole Faucher|publisher=[[Routledge]]|date=2019|ISBN=978-1-351-12426-3|via=[[Google Books]]|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=Us5wDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT134&lpg=PT134]|quote=Poskam (''Zepu'') County is 30 km to the east of Yarkand and is the petroleum and natural gas producing hub of southern Xinjiang. The Tajik Ethnic village in Poskam County consists of a few smaller settlements scattered around the Boyluq area.}}</ref> ({{ug|\u067e\u0648\u0633\u0643\u0627\u0645 \u0646\u0627\u06be\u0649\u064a\u0649\u0633\u0649}}), also '''Zepu County''' ({{zh|s={{linktext|\u6cfd\u666e|\u53bf}}}} from the [[SASM/GNC romanization#Uyghur|transliteration from Uyghur]] {{zh|s=\u6cfd\u666e\u52d2\u5584\u53bf}}), the former longer Chinese name as well, is a county in [[Kashgar Prefecture]], [[Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region]], [[China]]. Poskam County is bordered to the north and west across the [[Yarkand River]] by [[Yarkant County]] (Shache) and to the south and east by [[Kargilik County]] (Yecheng).\n\n==History==\nIn 1921, Poskam County was established.<ref name=\"xzqhposkam\"/>\n\nChina state media reported that in the early morning of October 24, 1999, two died, two were injured and major property damage was sustained at the Seyli (Saili) Township police office in a terrorist attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C43noQsQuTYC|title=Record of the Terrorist Activities of the \"East Turkisan\" Forces|ISBN=7-5085-0106-3|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=C43noQsQuTYC&pg=PA1998&lpg=PA1998]|quote=Early in the morning of October 24, 1999, terrorists attacked the police station in Saili Township, Zepu County, with guns, macheters, incendiary bottles and grenades. They shot one local security guard dead and wounded another, wounded a policeman and killed a criminal suspect in custody. After that, they burned ten rooms in the police station, and one jeep and three motorbikes belonging to the police.<br>The Saili Township Police Station after it was attacked.<br>An automobile burnt by the terrorists in the homicide-arson case in Zepu County.|via=[[Google Books]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5I2b_hrJO8sC|title=The ETIM: China's Islamic Militants and the Global Terrorist Threat|author=J. Todd Reed, Diana Raschke|publisher=[[Praeger Publishing]]|date=2010|ISBN=978-0-313-36540-9|quote=Early in the morning of October 24, 1999, terrorists attacked the police station in Saili Township, Zepu County, with guns, machetes, incendiary bottles and grenades. They shot one member of a local security guard dead and wounded another, wounded a policeman and killed a criminal suspect in custody. After that, they burned ten rooms, one jeep and three motorbikes belonging to the police station.|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=5I2b_hrJO8sC&pg=PA125&lpg=PA125 125]|via=[[Google Books]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://global.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201903/19/WS5c9033f0a3106c65c34ef4ae.html|title=Fighting terror, protecting human rights in Xinjiang|date=19 March 2019|website=[[China Daily]]|quote=On October 24, 1999, a group of terrorists armed with guns, knives, and explosive devices attacked a police station in Saili Township, Zepu County, Kashgar Prefecture. They threw incendiary bottles and explosive devices at the station, shot dead a public security guard and a criminal suspect in custody, injured a policeman and a public security guard, and burned 10 rooms, 1 jeep and 3 motorcycles in the police station.|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, [[China National Petroleum Corp]] announced plans to close Taxinan refinery.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-cnpc-refinery-closure/cnpc-to-mothball-refinery-in-xinjiang-for-environmental-safety-reasons-idUSKCN1RM07U|title=CNPC to mothball refinery in Xinjiang for environmental, safety reasons|date=10 April 2019|accessdate=6 April 2020|website=[[Reuters]]|authors=Chen Aizhu, Zhang Min|editor=Shreejay Sinha, Christian Schmollinger}}</ref>\n\n==Administrative divisions==\n[[File:Txu-oclc-6654394-nj-43-5th-ed.jpg|left|thumb|Map including Zepu (labeled as TSE-P'U (POSGAM)) and surrounding region from the [[International Map of the World]] ([[Army Map Service|AMS]], 1966)]]\nThe county includes two [[Town (China)|towns]] and ten [[Township (China)|townships]]:<ref name=\"xzqhposkam\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xzqh.org/html/show/xj/21318.html|script-title=zh:\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u5386\u53f2\u6cbf\u9769|website=XZQH.org|date=14 November 2014|accessdate=27 January 2020|quote={{lang|zh-hans|1921\u5e74\u7f6e\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf{...}2003\u5e74\uff0c\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u603b\u9762\u79ef999.66\u5e73\u65b9\u5343\u7c73{...}2010\u5e74\u7b2c\u516d\u6b21\u4eba\u53e3\u666e\u67e5\uff0c\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u5e38\u4f4f\u603b\u4eba\u53e3206936\u4eba\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d\uff1a\u6cfd\u666e\u954731665\u4eba\uff0c\u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u954710553\u4eba\uff0c\u5854\u91cc\u6728\u6cb9\u7530\u516c\u53f818173\u4eba\uff0c\u6ce2\u65af\u5580\u6728\u4e6120026\u4eba\uff0c\u4f9d\u739b\u4e6119628\u4eba\uff0c\u53e4\u52d2\u5df4\u683c\u4e6118571\u4eba\uff0c\u8d5b\u529b\u4e6116721\u4eba\uff0c\u4f9d\u80af\u82cf\u4e6119340\u4eba\uff0c\u56fe\u547c\u5176\u4e6110359\u4eba\uff0c\u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u4e6112713\u4eba\uff0c\u963f\u514b\u5854\u6728\u4e616652\u4eba\uff0c\u963f\u4f9d\u5e93\u52d2\u4e6111728\u4eba\uff0c\u5e03\u4f9d\u9c81\u514b\u5854\u5409\u514b\u65cf\u4e613564\u4eba\uff0c\u519c\u573a\u573a\u90e83776\u4eba\uff0c\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u826f\u79cd\u573a1873\u4eba\uff0c\u56ed\u827a\u573a1314\u4eba\uff0c\u56fd\u8425\u6797\u573a280\u4eba\u3002}}}}</ref><ref name=\"govposkamnames\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xjzp.gov.cn/P/C/10906.htm|script-title=zh:\u5173\u4e8e\u5370\u53d1\u300a\u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u5404\u4e61\u9547\u573a\u3001\u793e\u533a\u3001\u6751\u6807\u51c6\u5730\u540d\u300b\u7684\u901a\u77e5|language=ug,zh-hans|date=22 December 2017|accessdate=27 January 2020|website={{lang|zh-hans|\u6cfd\u666e\u653f\u5e9c\u7f51}}|quote=\u067e\u0648\u0633\u0643\u0627\u0645 \u0646\u0627\u06be\u0649\u064a\u0633\u0649\u062f\u0649\u0643\u0649 \u064a\u06d0\u0632\u0627\u060c \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0627\u0631 \u060c \u0645\u06d5\u064a\u062f\u0627\u0646\u0644\u0627\u0631\u060c \u0626\u0649\u062c\u062a\u0649\u0645\u0627\u0626\u0649\u064a \u0631\u0627\u064a\u06c7\u0646 \u060c \u0645\u06d5\u0645\u06c7\u0631\u0649 \u0643\u06d5\u0646\u0649\u062a\u0644\u06d5\u0631\u0646\u0649\u06ad \u0626\u06c6\u0644\u0686\u06d5\u0645\u0644\u0649\u0643 \u064a\u06d5\u0631 \u0646\u0627\u0645\u0649 \u6cfd\u666e\u53bf\u5404\u4e61\u3001\u9547\u3001\u573a\u3001\u793e\u533a\u3001\u884c\u653f\u6751\u6807\u51c6\u5730\u540d \u062e\u06d5\u0646\u0632\u06c7\u0686\u06d5 \u0626\u06c7\u064a\u063a\u06c7\u0631\u0686\u06d5 \u6c49\u6587 \u7ef4\u543e\u5c14\u6587 \u6cfd\u666e\u9547 \u067e\u0648\u0633\u0643\u0627\u0645 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0649\u0631\u0649{...}\u594e\u4f9d\u5df4\u683c\u9547 \u0643\u06c8\u064a\u0628\u0627\u063a \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0649\u0631\u0649{...}\u6ce2\u65af\u5580\u6728\u4e61 \u067e\u0648\u0633\u0643\u0627\u0645 \u064a\u06d0\u0632\u0633\u064